a poised female astronaut in a sleek, pearl-white EVA suit—front zipper partly open to hint at her curves, helmet visor lifted to reveal her serene face—strides confidently down a lamp-lit titanium walkway on the lunar surface; low-gravity dust plumes with each step while distant domed habitats glow soft magenta and cyan against the inky starfield, Earth hanging huge on the horizon. Camera starts waist-level, tracking backward as she advances, blue-violet floodlights outlining every carbon-fiber seam and chrome connector, reflections sliding across her visor. Subtle particle motes drift through micro-meteor scatter, suit LEDs pulse, and her gloved hand brushes a railing dusted with moondust before the lens pushes in on her calm smile—captured in 4K HDR, virtual 50 mm f/1.4 cine lens, ISO 800, RAW render.
